TIP1: Work with project!!!
This enables you to work with a Directory and allows you switch between files with cmd + p

TIP2: Multiple cursors
Hold cmd end select multiple lines do edit.

TIP3: Command Pallet cmd + shift + p

TIP4: Move current line up/down: “You can also move the curent line up and down the page using Ctrl + Cmd + Up/Down”

TIP5: Go to a specific line: You can jump to a line by using Ctrl + G and typing in the line #

